							<h4>Why You're Going to Love Ren'Py</h4>
							<ul class="features">
								<li class="icon fa-paper-plane-o">
									<h3>Free and <br />
									Open Source</h3>
									<p>Ren'Py is free to use with commercial and non-commercial games.</p>
									<p>There is no need to pay a fee to us or anyone else to distribute your Ren'Py game.</p>
									<p>Ren'Py has already been used with a half-dozen commercial games, and more are on the way.</p>
								</li>
								<li class="icon fa-laptop">
									<h3>Cross Platform<br />
									Computer and Mobile</h3>
									<p>One of Ren'Py's biggest advantages is that runs on almost every computer.</p>
									<p>There are three primary platforms we support: 
									<code>Windows XP+ (x86)</code>
									<code>Mac OS X 10.6+ (x86_64)</code>
									<code>Linux (x86, x86_64)</code>
								</li>
								<li class="icon fa-code">
									<h3>Simple Scripting  <br />
									Language
									</h3>
									<p>Ren'Py uses <code>Python</code> to let you define characters and images in a central place, making it easy to change the game.</p>
									<p>Scripts also provide consistency, ensuring that the placement of text and images does not inadvertently change throughout the game.</p>
									<p>Since Ren'Py's scripting language is text based, it can be typed out on any keyboard.</p>
								</li>
								<li class="icon fa-heart-o">
									<h3>Everyone Loves It</h3>
									<p>Hundreds of games have been released with Ren'Py, making it one of the most widely used visual novel engines in the world.</p>
									<p>There are now a large number of creators with Ren'Py experience, many of whom are willing to help fellow creators.</p>
									<p>The best place to go for support is the Ren'Py forum at the Lemma Soft Forums, which has more than 56,000 posts in over 9,500 threads.</p>
								</li>
